        '1. Merchandising Strategy & Forecast\na) Create focused product strategy and plan matching global strategy and local category growth needs.\nb) Project ecommerce merchandising growth and forecast down to category level for next 3-5 years.\nc) Identify product trends, formulate and plan the outlook of merchandising buying, selection, range, assortment and promotion in all ecommerce channels included O&O, marketplace and wholesale.\nd) Optimize channel strategy through business reviews across key functions and provide expert analysis and risk recommendations.\n\n2. Ecommerce Merchandising Planning& Allocation\na) Set the KPIs for the whole merchandising and each channel including discount, margin, and product mix.\nb) Drive the revenue and margin of ecommerce growth, responsible for inventory management and pricing.\nc) Develop and execute optimal merchandising strategy, product assortment, pricing, promotions, and merchandising plans by customer segment and by product. \nd) Determine OTB and buying plan for ecommerce channels by channel character and consumer profile.\ne) Execute OTB planning and by category sales forecast and participate in seasonal buying/ planning and category plan deliverables showcasing how seasonal assortment would come to life online.\nf) Strategize timing and fulfillment of replenishment for ecommerce channel in partnership with offline retail teams as to keep the optimal inventory structure.\n\n3. Analysis & Insight Provide\na) Consistently analyze on-going and historical sell-through/sell-in data as well as inventory structure by weekly /monthly/quarter to maximize product opportunities in ecommerce while controlling healthy ST%.\nb) Provide seasonal recaps on what worked, didn''t work and next steps from an analytics perspective as part of the seasonal hind sighting process.\nc) Give insights through product perspective and consumer behavior perspective across category, gender, channel, price range, discount and region to advise the actionable improve plan.\nd) Analyze competitive data through ecommerce database and competitors’ websites to evaluate site merchandising strategies, promotional tactics, consumer experience, and product presentation then translate findings into actionable plans.\ne) Provide necessary product training for the whole team and customer service vendor.\n\n4. Website Consumer Experience Optimize\na) Own and socialize seasonal calendars, landing pages, product walls, product pages, search results, etc. Optimizing online navigation, search results, creative touts and product presentation based on analytics (click-path, traffic, AUSP, ATV, conversion, etc.)\nb) Partner with the analytics team to define the analytics strategy. Review and analyze site traffic, conversion, and revenue daily, through merchandising, cart analysis, and cross-sell/up-sell strategies. Partner with the marketing team by creating engaging consumer journeys for online ads and emails. Partner with Global to Identify and recommend new site content and experiences to address our consumer needs.\nc) Collaborate with global experience teams to ensure seasonal content is ''retail right'' and drives the business in addition to telling key brand stories.\n\n5. Ecommerce Channel Operation & Cooperation\na) Tmall Operation.\nb) Kids Project Launch in China.\nc) Closely work with internal and external key functions.', 
