        'Jul 2014 - Oct 2016' || chr(9) || 'HR Manager\nMar 2013 - Jun 2014' || chr(9) || 'Assistant HR Manager\nFeb 2011 - Feb 2013' || chr(9) || 'HR Generalist\n\nResponsibilities:\n1. Daily HR support on full price stores cover Coach China (150 stores):\n* Working as a strategic role to provide professional HR support to business partner.\n* Deeply touching the business to provide the consulting and suggestion from HR perspective. \n* Provide feedback and advice to business clients on potential concerns and issues with appropriate options and solutions on employee relationship issues.\n* Working closely with C&B team to optimize employee compensation & benefit structure and define related regulation to accommodation with market changing.\n\n2. Recruitment:\n* Work collaboratively with business partners on new store opening, fully support with recruiting efforts. \n* As a recruitment head, be in charge of annual recruitment HC & budget landing according to the business development strategy. To devise cost-effective means to achieve recruitment demands, and fulfill requests within designated and agreed time period.\n* Initiated and drove the campus recruitment project from 2012 for build young talent pipeline. Independent completion of nationwide large-scale campus recruitment which successfully achieve the company business needs. \n* Leading “Retail management trainee program”, “Global Management Trainee exchange program”, “Retail recruitment We-chat project” and heavily involved in “Retail Labor Dispatch Employment Project” & “i-Shine recruitment webpage”.\n\n3. Talent review and development:\n* Conduct Retail Talent Review project twice a year. Work out the staff development plan, succession plan. \n* Partner with Retail Management team to review, manage and optimize team performance through Performance management, Succession Plan, Organization re-mapping, etc.\n* Partner with Global People Organization Development team to design various activities for the purpose of talent cultivation, development and retention not only on retail staffs but also extend to Area Manager level.\n\n4. Cost control:\n* Be in charge of annual budgeting control, oversee payment processing and partner with Finance Department to ensure each sum are properly tracked and administered. Support line manager to work out the annual budget for personnel cost.\n\n5. Policy refine & Process Simplification:\n* Review, develop and implement policies, guidelines and processes. \n* Working closely with line manager to establish HR policies, including recruiting, HR customer services and source data management, staff services.\n* Driving HR service efficiency by streamlining the process and constantly looking for feedback.', 
        null, null, 0, null, '20161101000000999000000001', '白子牙', to_date('23-04-2017 13:11:42', 'dd-mm-yyyy hh24:mi:ss'), 0, null, '0', 0, null, null, null);
